the expression of the emotions in man an.data-term: the expression of the emotions in man and animals

examples.en: 'Stop!' she cried.
He broke down and cried.
She cried loud and clear.
She suddenly broke down and cried.
I had cried oceans of tears.
Several of the children cried out in fright.
'Goodbye then!' he cried to her.
Seagulls on the cliffs cried loudly.
How he cried to me for help!
Her mascara smeared when she cried.
A ghostly voice cried Beware!.
The child cried out in excitement.
He was a happy child who rarely cried.
He cried silently while the song played.
He cried out at each stroke of the whip.
I cried like a child because I felt so alone.
She cried all the way home from school that day.
They cried tears of joy.
She moaned and cried out in pain.
The child cried out in a piteous voice.
Help, he cried, Get a doctor! Quick!
Nora laughed so much that she nearly cried.
Rex did all sorts of tricks. I cried when he died.
She cried down any party to which she wasn't invited.
Hooray! he cried when he heard that his team had won.
I'm afraid the committee has cried down your suggestion.
They would often browbeat the younger child until he cried.
Before the speaker was halfway through his speech, the crowd cried him down.
The distraught owner cried that she would do anything to get back her lost dog.
Upon hearing the offending ringing, the teacher sarcastically cried, Hark! Could that possibly be a cell phone?
